# Random User App

## Overview
The Random User App is an Android application built using Kotlin and Jetpack Compose.
It fetches and displays random user data, allowing users to search and view details of different
users.

## Features
- Display a list of random users
- Search functionality
- User detail view
- Offline support
- Dynamic theming based on system settings

## Technologies Used
- Kotlin
- Jetpack Compose
- Hilt for dependency injection
- Material3 for UI components
- AndroidX libraries
- Gradle for build automation

## Project Structure
- `app/src/main/java/com/android/randomuser/`: Contains the main source code for the application.
- `ui/components/`: Custom UI components used in the app.
- `ui/theme/`: Theme definitions and theming logic.
- `screens/listingScreen/`: Code related to the user listing screen.
- `common/api/`: Common utilities and API-related code.

## Getting Started
### Prerequisites
- Android Studio Ladybug | 2024.2.1 or later
- Android SDK
- Gradle

### Installation
1. Clone the repository:
    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/DineshKumarS15/random-user-app.git
    ```
2. Open the project in Android Studio.
3. Sync the project with Gradle files.
4. Build and run the project on an emulator or physical device.

## Usage
- Launch the app to see a list of random users.
- Use the search bar to filter users by name.
- Click on a user to view their details.

